BUFFERING\
- read/write a \'91block of bytes\'92 into a memory area called buffer\
- then read/write from that buffer (into the heap ?)\
- a buffer is a byte[]\
- default buffer size is 8192 bytes for java for Byte Streams and 8192 characters for Character Streams\
- buffer streams in java are chained to other streams that do the actual reading/writing\
\
